title: Sydney Airport passenger growth will continue to lag rivals: Moody's
text:
Sydney Airport passenger growth will ... Sydney Airport passenger growth will continue to lag rivals: Moody's Next Story Prev Story 3 hrs ago Read more: The Age 
Sydney Airport's international passenger traffic growth rate, which has fallen behind initial analyst forecasts this year, will continue to lag rivals Melbourne Airport and Brisbane Airport over the next 18 months, according to a report from Moody's. "Amongst the rated portfolio, Brisbane and Melbourne are the best-positioned airports to benefit from the stronger international growth," the credit ratings agency said.   The Age.
